jobs.long_description:
This artifact illustrates how to use [E2Clab experiment methodology](https://gitlab.inria.fr/E2Clab/e2clab) (and [EnOSlib](https://discovery.gitlabpages.inria.fr/enoslib/)) to deploy experiments on multi-platforms, such as: 

- Chameleon Cloud + CHI@Edge
- Grid'5000 + FIT IoT LAB

### In this example, you will learn how to:

1. Lease a machine on Grid'5000 / Chameleon Cloud (cloud server);
2. Lease a Raspberry Pi 3 on FIT IoT LAB / CHI@Edge (edge device);
3. Deploy MQTT broker + Deep Learning application on the cloud server for AI inference;
4. Deploy the MQTT client on the Raspberry Pi to send images to the cloud server;

### Access our article
[KheOps: Cost-effective Repeatability, Reproducibility, and Replicability of Edge-to-Cloud Experiments](https://hal.science/hal-04157720v1)
